.TH "snd_hda_get_conn_index" 9 "snd_hda_get_conn_index" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hda_get_conn_index \- get the connection index of the given NID
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hda_get_conn_index
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t mux "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "int recursive "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the HDA codec
.IP "mux" 12
NID containing the list
.IP "nid" 12
NID to select
.IP "recursive" 12
1 when searching NID recursively, otherwise 0
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Parses the connection list of the widget \fImux\fP and checks whether the
widget \fInid\fP is present.  If it is, return the connection index.
Otherwise it returns -1.
